  "text": "The methyl thiazole tetrazolium (MTT) assay (Mosmann 1983) was used to assess nucleoside analog cytotoxicity in siRNA transfected cells as described in [CITATION_1] ). After siRNA transfection, the cells were allowed to recover for 24 h before initiating the experiments, and drug incubations were carried out during 48 h. Absorbance was measured at a wavelength of 540 nm with the reference at 650 nm and an IC 50 value was calculated as the percent survival compared to control cells.",
